Fedora Cloud AMIs are available in both hardware virtual machine (HVM) and
paravirtual (PV) formats. HVM AMIs have access to enhanced networking, GPU
processing and performance-enhancing hardware extensions. Some instance
types (like Atomic images) are only available as HVM AMIs.
If you're unsure which image to choose, get the HVM format. It can provide the
same or better performance than PV images. Learn more...
